    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paper decorated by various means, which might include marbling, stencilling, dyeing, or block printing; to be used for endpapers, wallpaper, wrapping objects, or as a ground for printing or calligraphy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000020511/Hunter, Papermaking: History of an Ancient Craft (1947)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045262/Grove Dictionary of Art online (1999-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Papel decorado de distintas maneras, como ser por medio de jaspead, estarcido, tinturado o estampado por medio de tampones; que es empleado como papeles definitivos, papel mural, para envolver objetos o como base para impresión o caligrafía</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Papier dat op verschillende wijzen is gedecoreerd, bijvoorbeeld door marmering, sjabloneren, verven of blokdruk; te gebruiken voor papieren schutbladen, behang, cadeaupapier of als ondergrond voor drukwerk of kalligrafie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
